VALUES (
  164, 81.5, 88.0, 85.0, 87.0, 83.0, 64.0, 77.0,
  'Carbon Core CFRP technology - carbon fiber B-pillar and roof rail core with aluminum hood, doors, fenders. Mixed high-strength steel, aluminum, carbon fiber. 40 kg lighter than predecessor F01. Excellent torsional rigidity. Best panel gaps in BMW lineup at 3.5-4mm.',
  'Flagship NVH isolation. Hydraulic engine mounts standard. Acoustic laminated windshield. Pre-LCI: side glass NOT acoustically laminated - wind noise at highway speeds noted by C&D long-term test. Air suspension standard. B58 I6 is silky smooth. LCI added thicker laminated glass.',
  'Nappa leather standard. Merino individual leather optional. Real wood trim abundant. Excellent fit and finish. Soft-close doors. Ambient lighting. B&W audio optional. Same materials as 750i - no downgrade. Deductions: door check positions cost-cut vs F01, some hard plastics lower in cabin.',
  'Same BMW premium paint as 750i. Extra clear coat depth on Individual colors. Consistent application. No systemic corrosion issues. 12-year corrosion warranty. Well-protected structural steel.',
  'Same electronics complexity as 750i minus some N63-specific engine management. iDrive ID5 (pre-LCI) ages reasonably well. Display key is finicky and a known weak point. DSC module software faults (fixable). Gesture control adds complexity. Ambient lighting connectors can loosen.',
  'Nappa/Merino leather ages well with proper care. Real wood durable. Aluminum trim shows wear. Piano black surfaces scratch easily. Dashboard surfaces durable. Premium materials overall age gracefully.',
  '740i Q-score 81.5. Same excellent Carbon Core body and premium interior as 750i. Pre-LCI loses NVH points for non-laminated side glass (fixed in LCI). Build quality is flagship-level BMW. Electrical aging is the main concern - comparable to 750i minus some N63 engine management complexity.',
  'CLAR (Carbon Core)', 'Dingolfing (Germany)', 'CFRP adhesive + self-piercing rivet + laser weld', 3.7, 'Nappa leather standard', 6
);
